    "concept": "Choosing an Optimal Threshold: F1-Score and Business Context",
    "description": "Introduce the F1-score as a harmonic mean of precision and recall, useful when both are important. However, stress that for defect detection, a simple F1-score might not be enough. Explain how to choose a threshold based on the specific business context and the relative costs of false positives and false negatives. This often means prioritizing recall (to catch defects) even if it means accepting more false positives, up to a tolerable level. Model Collision: If a model has an F1-score of 0.8, but its precision is 0.95 and recall is 0.68, is this a good model for detecting critical security vulnerabilities? What if precision is 0.68 and recall is 0.95?",
